content:
Users Must Approve Access Every Time They Trigger the Device Flow

To improve security for the OAuth 2.0 device flow, we now prompt users to allow access to their Salesforce data every time they complete an action that initiates the flow. Before this change, for some integrations built with this flow, users who previously allowed an app to access their data sometimes weren't prompted for approval.

Where: This change applies to Lightning Experience (not available in all orgs) and Salesforce Classic in all editions.

How: This change applies only if the Permitted Users policy for the connected app or external client app is set to All users may self-authorize. If the policy is set to Admin approved users are pre-authorized, users still aren't prompted for approval.
title: Improving Security with Salesforce OAuth Device Flow
